cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper deals with reinforcement learning and planning methods for robots, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper proposes a method for learning task objectives from a few example images, which involves meta-learning a classifier. This approach can be used for both model-free reinforcement learning and visual model-based planning, which are relevant to all of the above sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.SY, in that order.
